[ In 2001, Pennsylvania reported 438 cases of animal rabies, according
to the Pennsylvania Animal Diagnostic Laboratory System. More than
half of the total of wild animal rabies cases appeared in raccoons, with
243 cases. - Mod.AS]
[This report brings back fond memories of gluing warning labels to
vaccine baits with weekend volunteers at the New York State Health
Dept. -- warnings for human finders to read. - Mod.JW]
